# Approach
If the array's length is less than 3, we could safely return the length of the array as any element present in it will either appear once or twice which satisfies the given condition.

Variable 'k' stores the length of 'in-place subarray' with unique elements which appears at most twice.

We begin with value of 'k' and 'i' as 2 as the array will have at most twice unique elements till 1.
Then we check 'nums[i]' with 'nums[k-2]' i.e current element with second element from length of 'in-place subarray' with unique elements and if they are not equal we store current element at end of in-place subarray
and increment k by 1.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

