Use two pointers i and j, i => to iterate through the array, j => to maintain writing pos for the next element.
While iterating through the array, keep count of elements having same value as current:
-if you encounter same element  and count is less than 2, then store the element in the next position
-else if you encounter a different element, then reset the count to 1 and store that element in the next position.
return j

