# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int removeDuplicates(int[] nums) {

        if(nums.length == 2)
        return nums.length;

        int fillindex=0;

        int len=0;

        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++)
        {
            int startindex=i;

            while(i<nums.length-1 && nums[i] == nums[i+1])
            {
                i++;
            }

            len = (i-startindex)+1;

            int counter = Math.min(len,2);

            while(counter>0 )
            {
                nums[fillindex]=nums[startindex];
                counter--;
                fillindex++;
            }
        }

        return fillindex;

    }
}
```

