# Intuition
The given array is sorted. This means next element will be either same element or bigger one. Store current element in a variable and keep comparing it with next element, also keep an eye that count does not exceed K (Here K is 2).

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Step 1: I come up with the idea that if I swap array for every duplicates, it will be costly, so I thought why not mark that place and swap everything at last.
There will be three cases as you can see in code
Case 1: Element of array is same as current element and count is still postive.
Case 2: Element of array is same as current element but count is not positive.
Case 3: Element of array is not equal to current.

Step 2: I sort the array. 
Step 3: Found the length using loop.
Step 4: Check Corner Cases for array size = 1 or 2 or 0;
You are done!!!

