We can copy the exact same solution from https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-duplicates-from-sorted-array/
The only trick is that we allow j to move forward n times when we find duplicates, where n = 2 for this exercise.
Make sure to add +1 to j when you return it because we want the length of the new array and not the last valid index.

**Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array (LC #26)**
```java
class Solution {
    public int removeDuplicates(int[] nums) {    
        if (nums == null || nums.length == 0)      
            return 0;

        int j = 0;        
        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {              
            if (nums[i-1] != nums[i]) {                  
                j++;
                nums[j] = nums[i];
            }    
        }

        return j;  
    }
}
```

