# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Use a map and a vector. Map will keep track of indexes of vals  and vector for vals . At remove operation just swap the number which is to be removed and the last one and then do pop_back and also update the index of last element in map. In this way we can remove the elements and also check the element is presnt or not. 
And for getRandom just return a random number presnt in the vector using `rand() ` function use `rand()%size` becuase rand() should be genrating indexes upto n-1 not beyond that .
