Whenever in questions it says O(1), I always think about HashMap. 


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Declare map in our concrete class, which is going to store the keys.
- Insert() - straight forward, if not present then add
- Remove() - straight forward, if present then delete
- GetRandom() - Need to think how we can get the randomKey, here we will find the length of the map, and using golang `rand` package we can get the random value in a range(in our case len of the map). We will introduce a counter which is going to tell us when to return the key.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
