# Intuition
Set can do all tasks except for getRandom().
Hence, the task is to establish the getRandom() function.

# Approach
Use an array to store values, use a Map to store val -> position_in_array.

Then for insert, array push is O(1), record position is easy.

For delete, Map delete is O(1), if element is at last, array pop is O(1), if it is not at the last position, swap the element at last position with it, update the position record in Map. Then pop() O(1).

To get random index, just use `Math.floor(Math.random() * array.length)`.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(1)

- Space complexity: O(n) where n is the maximum number of elements stored.

# Code
```
class RandomizedSet {
    valPos: Map<number, number> // value, index
    vals: number[]

    constructor() {
        this.valPos = new Map()
        this.vals = []
    }

    insert(val: number): boolean {
        if (this.valPos.has(val)) return false
        this.valPos.set(val, this.vals.length)
        this.vals.push(val)
        return true
    }

    remove(val: number): boolean {
        if (!this.valPos.has(val)) return false
        const pos = this.valPos.get(val)
        if (pos !== this.vals.length - 1) {
            const lastVal = this.vals[this.vals.length - 1];
            // swap position with the last element
            [this.vals[pos], this.vals[this.vals.length - 1]] = [this.vals[this.vals.length - 1], this.vals[pos]]
            this.valPos.set(lastVal, pos) // update position record
        }
        this.valPos.delete(val)
        this.vals.pop()
        return true
    }

    getRandom(): number {
        return this.vals[Math.floor(Math.random() * this.vals.length)]
    }
}
```

