In this question we are required to generete a special kind of data structure supporting following features:-
1. insert(val)
2. remove(val)
3. getRandom

All operations in O(1)

***Resolving getRandom : -***
here we have to return any random value that is present in our data structure. At first sight we observe that both insert and remove operation are satisfied by using set in O(1). Let us say that we are using unordered_set for first 2 operations, than we found that to get any random value from the set you have to iterate over it as set or even map does not support getting any value in O(1) but using vector you can achieve this, as with index value you can access any item in array in O(1).

Thus using set alone you cannot achieve all the 3 functions in required time. Thus use of set is eliminanted from above discussion.

Now we have to use 2 different data structure one is unordered map and another is a vector
key as the given val and value as index of the vector where that value is stored in vector.
So, when we remove anything from map we should also remove it from vector.
***Now you say that removing something from vector is not O(1) as we are required to do because when remove function is called we should delete our value both from map and vector. However in this case we can achieve delete operation in O(1), by moving swapping the value to be deleted with the last value in vector and then deleting the last value, deleting last value in vector is O(1) operation.***

***return v[rand()%v.size()];***
we use rand() function to generate any random value and mod it with vector size thus giving us random index value of vector.

```
class RandomizedSet {
public:
    /** Initialize your data structure here. */
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    vector<int> v;
    int currIndex = 0;

    RandomizedSet() {

    }

    /** Inserts a value to the set. Returns true if the set did not already contain the specified element. */
    bool insert(int val) {
        if(mp.find(val) == mp.end()){
            mp[val] = currIndex;
            v.push_back(val);
            currIndex++;
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    /** Removes a value from the set. Returns true if the set contained the specified element. */
    bool remove(int val) {
        if(mp.find(val) == mp.end()){
            return false;
        }
        int index = mp[val];
        int size = v.size();

        if(index ==  size-1){
            v.pop_back();
            mp.erase(val);
            return true;
        }
        else{
            mp.erase(val);
            mp[v[size-1]] = index;
            swap(v[index],v[size-1]);
            v.pop_back();
            currIndex--;
            return true;
        }     
    }

    /** Get a random element from the set. */
    int getRandom() {
        return v[rand()%v.size()];
    }
};

