# Intuition
We can use the set but we cannot access the random index directly from the set without traversing it..so this will result in more time complexity.

# Approach
We can use an unordered_map and vector in the insertion we keep track of the indices and we add the value to vector and add the index of the element's index to the map and in the deletion we change the key index to the last index and replace it with the last value and we just delete and erase from the map..so in random we can return a value by rand() funtion.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
Insertion-->O(1)
Deletion-->O(1map)
Random-->O(1)
- Space complexity:
map-->O(n)
vector-->O(n)

