solutions.content:
- The max heap will keep lesser half of current subarray
- The min heap will keep greater half of current subarray
- Inserting and Removing logic: We insert/remove from max heap if the element is equal to or less than the peek value of max heap. Otherwise insert/remove from min heap.
- Rebalancing logic : Max heap needs to have just one more element than min heap or they need to have same number of elements
- Getting median logic: If the two heaps have same # of elements, median is division of the peek values from min heap and max heap. Otherwise it is the peek value from Max Heap.

- TC: O (n * k) because we iterate through n values of the array and each time we iterate we are performing a remove/add from heap which is O(log (k/2 +1)) since at most there are k/2 + 1 elements in each heap but we are also removing a specified value from the heaps so there's also a O(k) to search through the heap. 
- SC: O (log k) due to the two heaps maintaining at most k values 

```
class Solution {

    PriorityQueue<Integer> minHeap = new PriorityQueue<>();
    PriorityQueue<Integer> maxHeap = new PriorityQueue<>(Collections.reverseOrder());

    public double[] medianSlidingWindow(int[] nums, int k) {

        //length of resulting array, just think about how long it should be by writing out array and indexing 
        double[] res = new double[nums.length-k+1];
        int resIdx = 0;
        int l = 0; 
        for(int r=0; r<nums.length; r++) {

            if(maxHeap.size() == 0 || nums[r] <= maxHeap.peek()) {
                maxHeap.add(nums[r]);
            } else {
                minHeap.add(nums[r]);
            }
            //we rebalance heaps anytime we add to the heap or remove from the heap
            rebalanceHeaps();
			//this is when our right pointer first has k values and will continue to have k values until end of loop
            if(r-k+1 >= 0) {

                if(maxHeap.size() == minHeap.size()) {
                    //(maxHeap.peek() + minHeap.peek())/2.0 will cause an integer overflow with maximum integer numbers
                    res[resIdx] = maxHeap.peek()/2.0 + minHeap.peek()/2.0;
                } else {
                    res[resIdx] = maxHeap.peek();
                }
                resIdx++;

                //element to remove from sliding window will start at 0 and increment by 1
                int elementToBeRemoved = nums[l];

                //removing logic same as adding logic
                if (elementToBeRemoved <= maxHeap.peek()) {
                  maxHeap.remove(elementToBeRemoved);
                } else {
                  minHeap.remove(elementToBeRemoved);
                }
                l++;
                //again rebalance the heaps since we removed
                rebalanceHeaps();

            }
        }
        return res; 
    }

    public void rebalanceHeaps() {

        if (maxHeap.size() > minHeap.size() + 1)
          minHeap.add(maxHeap.poll());
        else if (maxHeap.size() < minHeap.size())
          maxHeap.add(minHeap.poll());
    }


}
