# Intuition
1. For Any answer we can confirm there is atleast answer+1 rabbit.
for Example: If a rabbit say there are 3 rabbit as same colour as it. We know there are atleast 3 other Rabbit + 1 Rabbit who is answering=4 rabbits
2. As we considering minimum rabbit case. At Very max N+1 rabbit can answer "N" and can belong to Same colour.
# Approach
1. We will store all answers in HashMap, as key. And as value we will store how many other rabbits have answered the same. So for example 3 we can say there can be maximum 3 "other rabbits" who can answer 3.
2. When ever we see a new answer, we can say these rabbits belongs to a unseeen colour group. and we will add answer+1 to our final answer. And we will reset the value for that answer key to 0.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N) One Pass

- Space complexity:
O(N)
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int numRabbits(int[] answers) {
        Map<Integer,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        int count=0;
        for(int ans: answers){
            if(map.getOrDefault(ans,ans)==ans){
                count+=ans+1;
                map.put(ans,0);
            }
            else{
                map.put(ans,map.get(ans)+1);
            }
        }
        return count;

    }
}
```

