# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
    Trying to make a group with same value in array. If group size is larger than value+1 (value in that group) , then modValue will be counted. Extra (value+1 - modValue) will be added to answer if modValue exists.  
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
    1.Sort the array first
    2.At first consider same value in one color group
    3.Count the same value in each group
    4.(Count % (value+1) = modValue)
    5.If modValue non zero then add ((value+1) - modValue) to extra
    6.Finally return array.size + extra 
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(nlong(n))
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(1)
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int numRabbits(vector<int>& answers) {
        sort(answers.begin() , answers.end());
        int cnt = 1,len = 0, sum=0, extra=0;

        for(int i=0; i<answers.size(); i++)
        {
            if( i==answers.size()-1 || answers[i]!=answers[i+1]){
                int modValue;
                modValue = cnt%(answers[i]+1);
               if(modValue) extra+=(answers[i]+1-modValue);
                cnt=1;
            }else{
                cnt++;
            }
        }

        return answers.size()+extra ;

    }
};
```

