Hence we can say that we can find the minimum no of rabbits by Making this algorithm
count=count+((e.getKey()+1)*(e.getValue()/(e.getKey()+1)));  > dividing rabbit ans with its total occurence .
If **occurence %key !=0** i.e (e.getValue()%(e.getKey()+1)!=0)->It means there is one unique color rabbit not seen in the array. we add the rabbit count as seen in previous example [4,4,4,4,4,**4]**

