```
Key Idea is, If a rabbit let name it Rabbit1 says there are x like me.
The Rabbit1 can be considered of a group of (x+1) of the same color.

Example- If Rabbit1 says there are 10 like me, Rabbit is a part of group of 11 Rabbits of same color.
So if you ask the other 10 Rabbits of the group of 11 Rabbits for Rabbit1.
Let's name them Rabbit1, Rabbit2..........,Rabbit11.


Let's Consider asking those 11 Rabbits same question, How many are like you.
1. Asking Rabbit1.
2. Asking Rabbit1 and Rabbit2
3. Asking Rabbit2 and Rabbit3.
4. Asking all 11 Rabbits

They all will answer same thing, There are 10 like me.
So if 2 Rabbits say there are 10 like me, Number of rabbit = 11.
So if 3 Rabbits say there are 10 like me, Number of rabbit = 11.

So we have no problem if any number of rabbits among 11 or even all 11 say there are 10 like me.

Supose a 12th Rabbit named RabbitNew comes and says there are 10 like me.
Now comes the problem, It cannot be the part of the previous 11 Rabbits(Rabbit1 to Rabbit2).
Else there answer would change to 11 like me, 
Or group of 12 Rabbits, i.e Group of 11 Rabbits(Rabbit1 to Rabbit2) + RabbitNew = 12.

So Basically if you store in Hashmap<How many like me(x), Frequency(f)>
As long as f is less than or equal to (x+1) for a particular x all rabbits are part of same group of (x+1) member.

If at any point f becomes x+2, We assume having two groups.(x+1) Members Group I and 1 Member Group II.
We count Group I straight away and store it in our answer, And Make frequency back to 1 for x.
