The code is based on the intuition of how many rabbits say a specific number. If the number of rabbits saying a specific number is more than one more than the number, then we understand that there are rabbits of a newly found colour. We use a `HashMap` to store this information, if there is a newly found number, then that is accounted for in the total count.
```
class Solution {
    public int numRabbits(int[] answers) {
        int total = 0;
        int n = answers.length;
        if(n==0)
            return 0;
        HashMap<Integer,Integer> count = new HashMap<>();
        for(int a:answers){
            if(count.containsKey(a)){
                int k = count.get(a);
                if(k <= a){
                    count.put(a,k+1);
                }else{
                    total += a+1;
                    count.put(a,1);
                }
            }else{
                total += a+1;
                count.put(a,1);
            }
        }

        return total;
    }
}
