def numRabbits(answers: Array[Int]): Int = {
  ((answers groupBy (x => x)).toList foldLeft 0) { (a, c) => 
    val numGroups = (c._2.length - 1) / (c._1 + 1) + 1
    a + numGroups * (c._1 + 1)
  }
}
```
Each rabbit is grouped based on their answer. For any group n, up to n + 1 rabbits may be of the same colour. The minimum amount of rabbits occurs when each rabbit that answered is the same colour as other ones that answered with the same number. The rabbits that are left over must also be part of a group of n + 1 rabbits, where the remaining ones must not have answered. The number of these colour groups is  the ceiling of the number of rabbits in group n divided by n + 1, and the number of rabbits in total is the number of those groups multiplied by the group size (n + 1).

Thus, summing the min rabbits in each answer group gives the min total.

