## Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
For any unique answer value we can confirm that there are answer+1 rabbits. Ex: [1,2,3] - Total number of rabbits will be: 2+3+4 = 9

For answers will same value: Ex- [2,2,4] - The answer[0] and answer[1] belong to the same color group and answer[2] belongs to another color group. 

Given 1 <= answers.length <= 1000. Maximum number of possible groups are 1000 based on the given constraints.

So maintain two arrays - to check the number of rabbits counted in a particular color group and another to check if that group is full or not. If the group is full then mark that group as false.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
**countArray[1000]**- Used to  count the number of rabbits added to each group. 

**visited[10000]** - Used to check wether that particular color group is still being filled or is already full.

If the color - 2(color group with two neighbors) is not visited then we reset the countArray of color 2 to zero and visisted of color 2 as true and add 2+1 max possible rabbits to count(total count of rabbits).

Next time color 2 is seen in the answer array - It checks whether color 2 is full? (countArray[2]!=2)
So, it increases the value of countArray[2]++ and mark color 2 as visited.

When the color 2 group is full : countArray[2] == 2 and visited[2] == true,
it means there no more space for same number of neighbors rabbits to be together. So, we reset the countArray[2] == 0 and visisted[2] ==false and tart a new color group with 2 neightbors - So add 2+1 rabbits of this group to the total count.

