Compute the cubes' **contact surface area difference** in x and y directions, recpectively; as for the area seen along z-axis, count the number of non-zero values and times 2.

```
    public int surfaceArea(int[][] grid) {
        int x = 0, y = 0, z = 0, n = grid.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; x += grid[n - 1][i], y += grid[i][n - 1], ++i) { // do NOT forget the surface at (n - 1, i) and (i, n - 1).
            for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
                x += Math.abs(grid[j][i] - (j > 0 ? grid[j - 1][i] : 0)); // dummy value for grid[-1][i] is 0.
                y += Math.abs(grid[i][j] - (j > 0 ? grid[i][j - 1] : 0)); // dummy value for grid[i][-1] is 0.
                z += grid[i][j] > 0 ? 2 : 0;
            }
        }
        return x + y + z;    
    }
```

