Since there might be **holes** in shapes, whose surface areas couldn't be projected.
We CANNOT use the 2*[883. Projection Area of 3D Shapes](https://leetcode.com/problems/projection-area-of-3d-shapes/) to solve it : (
.

**Intuition** 

We have to focus on **overlapping** occurrence then.

```
Assume there are n cubes and k times of overlapping happens
-> surface area = 6*n-2*k.
```
>Note: don't forget 3-directions all may overlap.
A cube of height `h` **has already overlaps`h-1`times ITSELF**!

```
var surfaceArea = function(grid) {
    let cube=0, overlap=0;
    for(let i=0; i<grid.length; i++){
        for(let j=0; j<grid[i].length; j++){
            cube+=grid[i][j];
            if(i>0){overlap+=Math.min(grid[i][j], grid[i-1][j]);} // x-direction
            if(j>0){overlap+=Math.min(grid[i][j], grid[i][j-1]);} // y-direction
			if(grid[i][j]>1){overlap+=grid[i][j]-1}; // z-direction
        }
    }
    return cube*6-overlap*2;
};
```

