Every tower with height greater than 1 will contribute 6 faces for the first cube; every cube after the first will add 4 more faces because there is one face that touches every two adjacent cubes that will not contribute to surface area.
Every tower that borders with adjacent towers in each direction, up, down left, right, will have Math.min(tower_height, adjacent_tower_height) faces hidden, thus not contribute to surface area; this will be accounted for by subtracting Math.min(tower_height, adjacent_tower_height) from surface area twice, once for tower, once for adjacent_tower, in their respective loop iterations. 
