If only 1 cube is present at 1 index, surface area =6
if 2 cubes are present, surface area = 12-2(overlapping area) = 10
If 3 cubes are present, surface area = 18-4(overlapping area) = 14

Hence if n cubes are present, surface area=  4n+2  ... derived by looking at the above values.

Now we have to remove common area of adjacent blocks.

Hence, if a block of height 2 has block of height 1 adjacent to it, we subtract 1 from count. (ie minimum of the heights of these two  ie 1 in this case)
Similarly when we come across the same block of height 1 again in loop, it will have height 2 block adjacent to it. Again minimum will be subtracted(ie 1 in this case).

Hence overall, the 2 common areas are removed.
Similar is applied to all blocks and their adjacents in all 4 directions. For the boundary blocks, it is applied whereever applicable.

