**----------------------- Let's first look at the `2D version` of this problem [463. Island Perimeter](https://leetcode.com/problems/island-perimeter/description/) -----------------------**
**Soution 1 brute force**
   * for `each cell with non zero value:` 
   * for each `direction:` if the next cell is `out boundary` or is `0`, we add `1` to res
```
class Solution {
    static final int[][] dirs = new int[][] {{0,-1}, {-1,0}, {0,1}, {1,0}};
    public int islandPerimeter(int[][] grid) { 
        int perimeter = 0;
        for (int r = 0; r < grid.length; r++) {
            for (int c = 0; c < grid[0].length; c++) {
                if (grid[r][c] == 1) {
                    for (int[] dir : dirs) {
                        int nr = r + dir[0], nc = c + dir[1];
                        if (offBoundary(nr, nc, grid) || grid[nr][nc] == 0) perimeter++;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return perimeter;
    }

    private boolean offBoundary(int r, int c, int[][] grid) {
        return r < 0 || r >= grid.length || c < 0 || c >= grid[0].length;
    }
}
```

**Soution 2 accumulate and retract**
   * we traverse each cell row by row, col by col and `update the result dynamically`
   * for `each cell with non zero value`, let's first `accumulate` it's contribution to total perimeter: `res += 4`
   * if `up cell is non zero`, we do retraction: `res -= 2`
   * if `left cell is non zero`, we do retraction: `res -= 2`
   ![image](https://s3-lc-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/users/meganlee/image_1536383412.png)

```
class Solution {
    public int islandPerimeter(int[][] grid) {
        int res = 0;
        for (int r  = 0; r < grid.length; r++) {
            for (int c = 0; c < grid[0].length; c++) {
                if (grid[r][c] == 1) {
                    res += 4;
                    if (r > 0 && grid[r - 1][c] == 1) res -= 2;
                    if (c > 0 && grid[r][c - 1] == 1) res -= 2;
                }
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```


**-------- Now let's look at the this problem, which is exactly follow up as a `3D version` of [463. Island Perimeter](https://leetcode.com/problems/island-perimeter/description/) -----------------------**
similarly
**Soution 1 brute force**
   * for `each cell with non zero value:` res += `2 (1 for top, 1 for bottom)`
   * for each `direction/side:` we get a `nextHeight`, if `curHeight > nextHeight` we add exposed area: `curHeight - nextHeight` to res 
```
class Solution {
    static final int[][] dirs = new int[][] {{0,-1}, {-1,0}, {0,1}, {1,0}};
    public int surfaceArea(int[][] grid) {
        int area = 0;
        for (int r = 0; r < grid.length; r++) {
            for (int c = 0; c < grid[0].length; c++) {
                if (grid[r][c] != 0) { // only consider NON-ZERO cubes
                    int curHeight = grid[r][c];
                    area += 2; // top & bottom
                    for (int[] dir : dirs) {
                        int nr = r + dir[0], nc = c + dir[1];
                        int nextHeight = getHeight(nr, nc, grid);
                        area += (curHeight > nextHeight) ? curHeight - nextHeight : 0; // side surface
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return area;
    }

    private int getHeight(int r, int c, int[][] grid) {
        if (r < 0 || r >= grid.length || c < 0 || c >= grid[0].length) return 0; // out of bounds
        else return grid[r][c];
    }
```

**Soution 2 accumulate and retract**
   * we traverse each cell row by row, col by col and `update the result dynamically`
   * for `each cell with non zero value`, let's first `accumulate` it's contribution to total area: `res += 2 + 4 * side`
   * if `up cell is non zero`, we do retraction: `res -= 2 * min(upHeight, curHeight)`
   * if `left cell is non zero`, we do retraction: `res -= 2 * min(leftHeight, curHeight)`
![image](https://s3-lc-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/users/meganlee/image_1536384442.png)
```
class Solution {
    static final int[][] dirs = new int[][] {{0,-1}, {-1,0}, {0,1}, {1,0}};
    public int surfaceArea(int[][] grid) {
        int res = 0;
        for (int r = 0; r < grid.length; r++) {
            for (int c = 0; c < grid[0].length; c++) {
                if (grid[r][c] != 0) {
                    res += 2 + 4 * grid[r][c];
                    if (r > 0 && grid[r - 1][c] != 0) res -= 2 * Math.min(grid[r][c], grid[r - 1][c]); // up
                    if (c > 0 && grid[r][c - 1] != 0) res -= 2 * Math.min(grid[r][c], grid[r][c - 1]); // left
                }
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

