# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- If any cell have value non zero, then increase the ans with 2 for the top and bottom sides.
- Then check all 4 sides of it, if the sides are not in range of 0 to n, means the cell is corner one, so add the grid[i][j] into ans;
- Else compare it with its neighbour and if the current cell is higher then neighbour than, add the diff in the ans.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int surfaceArea(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int n = grid.size(), ans = 0;
        int dr[] = {0,1,0,-1};
        int dc[] = {1,0,-1,0};
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            for(int j=0; j<n; j++){
                if(grid[i][j] != 0)
                    ans += 2;

                for(int k=0; k<4; k++){
                    int row = i + dr[k];
                    int col = j + dc[k];
                    if(row >= 0 && row < n && col >= 0 && col < n){
                        if(grid[row][col] < grid[i][j]){
                            ans += grid[i][j] - grid[row][col];
                        }
                    }
                    else ans += grid[i][j];
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

