# Intuition
In this problem we have to given a grid matrix in which grid[i][j] represent the number of cube of size 1x1x1 is kept at position [i][j].
Now we have to find the uncovered surface area of the structure formed after placing all the cube as instructed (including bottom part).

# Approach
for finding total surface area of the cube we have divided the problem into three sub problem.
1. if any block exit at any position we will add its bottom surface area and upper surface area does not matter how tall the cube tower is. for this we will check if any cube exist under two for loop which will run for all the through the grid and add 2 to area.
2. In the second part we will add the vertical surface area along the boundary.
3. Now, in the third part we are left with the vertical area if we there is is height diferenence in the cube tower height. for this we have picked each tower and checked how many tower does exist beside the tower and smaller that the picked up tower. If any tower exist and also smaller then we will add vertical area which will equal to the height difference of the tower.
4. And then we have returned area.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n2)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int surfaceArea(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int a = grid.size();
        long int area = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i<a; i++){
            area+=grid[0][i]; //adding vertical area of in first row;
            area+=grid[a-1][i]; //adding vertical area in least row;
            area+=grid[i][0]; //adding vertical area in first column
            area+=grid[i][a-1]; // adding vertical area in last column
            for(int j = 0; j<a; j++){
            //adding bottom and upperpart of the cube if any cube exist does not matter how tall the cube tower is its upper and lower lower suraface area exist.
                if(grid[i][j]){
                    area+=2;
                }
//checking does any cube tower exist and is smaller than curent tower then adding the vertical surface area.
//for checking in all the four direction we have used four condition
                if(j+1<a){
                    if(grid[i][j]>grid[i][j+1]){
                        area+=(grid[i][j]-grid[i][j+1]);
                    }
                }
                if(i+1<a){
                    if(grid[i][j]>grid[i+1][j]){
                        area+=(grid[i][j]-grid[i+1][j]);
                    }
                }
                if(j-1>=0){
                    if(grid[i][j]>grid[i][j-1]){
                        area+=(grid[i][j]-grid[i][j-1]);
                    }
                }
                if(i-1>=0){
                    if(grid[i][j]>grid[i-1][j]){
                        area+=(grid[i][j]-grid[i-1][j]);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return area;
    }
};
```

